        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 33</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex033-P142r-L11_trl" n="11"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.002.032.trl.xml#Ex032-P142r-L11_trl" />
                        <l>to Moses, saying, ‘Go, go up from here, you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and the people whom you have brought out from the land of Egypt, to the
                            land which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             I swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             “I will give it to your offspring.”</l>
                        <l n="2">And I will send
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             an angel before you — and I will drive out the Canaanite, the Amorite,
                            and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             the Hittite, and the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite —</l>
                        <l n="3">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             To a land flowing |with| milk and honey, because my divine Presence
                            will not go
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             in the midst of you, because you are a stiff-necked people, lest I
                            consume
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             you in the way.’</l>
                        <l n="4">And the people heard this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             evil word, and they mourned, and no man did put
                            <milestone unit="page" n="142v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             on him his ornaments.</l>
                        <l n="5">And the Lord said to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             ‘Say to the children of Israel, “You are a stiff-necked people.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             If <seg type="commented" corresp="#Ex-033-seg001_trl" />for a blink of
                            an eye<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Ex-033-seg001_trl" /><ref n="1"
                                target="#Ex-033-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> my divine Presence
                            should go in the midst of you, I would consume you.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             And now take off your ornaments from you, and I will know
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             what to do to you.”’</l>
                        <l n="6">And the sons of Israel stripped themselves
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             of their ornaments from Mount Horeb |onward|.</l>
                        <l n="7">And Moses
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             took the tent, and pitched it for himself outside the camp,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             to make it be far off from the camp, and called it the tent of meeting.
                            And it was:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             everyone who sought to ask the word of the Lord went out to the tent of
                            meeting
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             which was outside the camp.</l>
                        <l n="8">And it would be: when Moses went out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to the tent, all the people rose up and stood each man
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             at his tent door, and looked after Moses, until he came
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             to the tent.</l>
                        <l n="9">And it would be: as Moses came
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             to the tent, the pillar of cloud descended and stood at the door
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             of the tent, and the Lord spoke with Moses.</l>
                        <l n="10">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             all the people saw the pillar of cloud standing
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             at the tent door, and all the people rose up and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             worshiped, each man in his tent door.</l>
                        <l n="11">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             the divine Presence of the Lord spoke to Moses mind to mind, as a man
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             speaks to his friend. And he turned again to the camp. And his servant
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             Joshua, son of Nun, who served the service of a young man,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="143r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             did not depart from the tent.</l>
                        <l n="12">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             And Moses said to the Lord, ‘See, you say to me, “Bring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             up this people,” and you have not let me know
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             whom you will send with me. And you have said, “I know you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             by name, and you have also found favour in my sight.”</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="13">And now, if I have now found
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             favour in your sight, let me know, I beg you, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Ex-033-seg002_trl" />the way you will act
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             toward those whom you created<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Ex-033-seg002_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Ex-033-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> that I may find favour
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in your eyes <seg type="commented" corresp="#Ex-033-seg003_trl" />when
                            I beg before you for your people<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Ex-033-seg003_trl" /><ref n="3" target="#Ex-033-fn3_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             And see that this kingdom is your people.’</l>
                        <l n="14">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And the Lord said, ‘My directions will go |with you|, and I will give
                            you rest.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="15">And Moses said to the Lord, ‘If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             your directions are not going among us, do not bring us out from
                            here.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="16">And by what will it be known here that I have found favour
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             in your eyes, I and your people? Lo, in that your divine Presence goes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             with us. And we shall be separated, I and your people,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             from all the people that are on the face of the earth.’</l>
                        <l n="17">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             And the Lord said to Moses, ‘I will do this thing that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             you have spoken as well, because you have found favour in my eyes,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and I have known you by name.’</l>
                        <l n="18">And Moses said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             to the Lord, ‘I pray you, show me your glory.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="143v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="19">And the Lord said, ‘I will make all my goodness pass
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             before you, and I will call the name of the Lord before you. And I
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             will have mercy on the man who is equal to my mercy, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             I will be gracious to the man who is equal to my grace.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="20">And the Lord said, ‘You cannot see
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             my directions, because neither man nor angel sees me.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="21">And the Lord said, ‘Lo, there is a place by me,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             and you shall stand on the rock.</l>
                        <l n="22">And it shall be,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             while my glory passes by, I will put you in a cleft of the rock, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             I will cover you with my command until my divine Presence has passed
                            by.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="23">And I will take away my command, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             you shall see my hindmost creation, but my directions
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex033-P143v-L13_trl" n="13"
                                next="ADub.III.73.002.034.trl.xml#Ex034-P143v-L13_trl" />
                             will not be seen.’</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
